news.title: Andhra Pradesh government keen to complete registrations of plots under LPS
news.para: The govt is of the view that delay in completion of registration process is creating more litigations and hurdles to the Capital Region Development Authority (CRDA) in taking up developmental work.

news.title: Aggrieved home-buyers must name promoters in complaint: Karnataka HC
news.para: The idea is to cheat homebuyers or avoid paying compensation to them for either delay in delivering the flats or for sub-standard quality or for not honouring the commitment made at the time of signing an agreement.

news.title: Incuspaze raises Rs 67 crore in maiden funding round
news.para: This investment will significantly bolster our capabilities to provide top-tier workspace solutions tailored to enterprises, MSMEs, and startups.

news.title: Mumbai: Court denies bail to owner of Kamala Mills in cheating case
news.para: “The offence is grave in nature. If the accused is released on bail, he may impede the ongoing investigation by tampering with evidence and influencing prosecution witnesses,” the magistrate remarked.

news.title: KSUM all set to submit DPR to Kerala government for tech startup hub at Technocity
news.para: The report earmarks five pivotal sectors for the hub: aerospace, healthcare, agriculture and food, digital media and entertainment, and energy.

news.title: Residents of Baliawas warn of blockade if C&D waste plan not scrapped
news.para: Residents organised a panchayat on Saturday and said they will meet senior officials from the civic body to present their demand.

news.title: Land deals drop 57%to 325 acres in Q1 FY25: Anarock
news.para: Real estate consultant Anarock pointed out that the general elections and the heated land prices seem to have dented the appetite for land acquisition for developers and other entities in the second quarter of 2024.

news.title: EOW registers case against Zeus Housing's directors for cheating buyers of Rs 67 crore
news.para: The police said that the two directors of Zeus Housing and Construction Pvt Ltd took money from flat buyers with assurances of constructing a 44-storey tower.

news.title: Cidco offers 48 plots across Navi Mumbai on lease for residential, industrial activities
news.para: ​In addition, 218 shops in various Cidco housing complexes are also on offer. While the online registration for the scheme for the sale of plots began last week, the registration for shops kicked off on July 16.

news.title: Suryoday Small Finance Bank buys office space in Navi Mumbai for Rs 100 crore
news.para: The office space spread over a total 12 units across three wings of one of the towers of commercial complex L&T Seawoods Grand Central has a total carpet area of nearly 60,000 sq ft.

news.title: Goa: SC reverts challenge to ODPs of five villages to HC, says expedite disposal
news.para: The SC in May had stayed the interim order of the HC which had stayed development based on permissions or conversions granted under outline development plan (ODPs) notified on Dec 15, 2022 for Calangute, Candolim, Arpora, Nagoa, and Parra.

news.title: JK Cement's net profit surges 67% to Rs 184.82 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations edged up 1.62 per cent at Rs 2,807.57 crore during the quarter under review. It was Rs 2,762.63 crore a year ago.

news.title: Panchkula citizens' body to move HC against stilt+four floor constructions policy
news.para: CWA president S K Nayyar, while chairing a meet at Red Bishop in Sector 1 with all the directly affected residents, said the government is not listening to the sufferers.

news.title: SEIAA asks Gurugram DC to investigate environmental clearance granted for Global City
news.para: The action followed a complaint by an environmentalist, who alleged that the Haryana State Industrial and Infrastructure Development Corporation (HSIIDC) may have provided misleading information to secure a clearance from the Centre.

news.title: Switzerland’s Schindler aims to employ more people in India: CEO
news.para: Urbanising India is a key growth market for liftmakers such as Schindler, particularly as neighbouring China struggles with a real estate crisis.

news.title: Government will introduce tenant verification bill in next assembly session: Goa CM
news.para: “In the coming assembly session we will introduce the bill. We will have clauses so that people have a little fear about being arrested and being fined Rs10,000,” said Sawant.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body’s delegation studies BBMP’s property tax software & digitization efforts
news.para: Led by KMC Commissioner Manjulekshmi, the delegation was welcomed by BBMP Joint Commissioner Lakshmidevi at the BBMP central office.

news.title: Kolkata: Less footpath space for stacking building materials in New Town
news.para: The New Town Kolkata development authority (NKDA) on Friday issued a notification in this regard. A SOP to follow the order will be notified next week, officials said.
